data.name: UI03_FormattingCodes.Text
data.value:
Formatting Codes:
"$RS" -> Release type (for example "Stable") "$MV" -> Major version (for example "2.10") "$BN" -> Build number (for example "1200.00") "$CV" -> Complete version (for example "2.10.1200.00-rtmbld-08") "$BDD" -> Build date day (for example "13") "$BDM" -> Build date month (for example "04" ("04" for "April")) "$BDY" -> Build date year (for example "2021") "$BDV" -> Build date in long format (for example "13 April 2021") "$BDC" -> Combined build date from build string (for example "130421") "$ABS" -> Build string (the one you can see in the "About SMWMTL" window) "$CN" -> Release codename (for example "Québec")
You can write these codes in the custom Title text field. (These codes are case sentitive, so write them in capital letters)
